circumstances: The crew was preparing the aircraft to perform a cargo flight to Calgary (flight NRL920). While taxiing, the aircraft went out of control, collided with a parked Ameriflight Piper PA-31 before coming to rest against a metallic fence. Both pilots were uninjured while the aircraft was damaged beyond repair.
probable_cause: The NTSB confirmed that no investigation have been conducted about this incident. Thus, the cause remains unknown.
